OL,6,F"When the union's evidence is
OL,7,Fcomplete, the union will consult our
OL,8,Flawyers to take necessary steps to
OL,9,Fensure that this matter is referred
OL,10,Fback to the court for a thorough
OL,11,Freview at a hearing on a later date.
OL,13,F"The hearing last Friday evening
OL,14,Finvolved the council being able to
OL,15,Fpresent a large amount of material,
OL,16,Fwhich was disclosed to the union late
OL,17,Fon Friday afternoon. Unite was given
OL,18,Fno proper notice of the hearing and
OL,19,Fhad no opportunity to present our side
OL,20,Fof the case. That will be redressed on
OL,21,Fthe basis set out above."
